Fete for the wedding of Princess Marie Amelie d Orleans (1865-1951

XEE4192868 Fete for the wedding of Princess Marie Amelie d Orleans (1865-1951) and Duke Charles Ferdinand de Bragance (1863-1908) at the Palais Royal in Paris in 1886. He became King Charles (Carlos) I of Portugal. A newspaper. Engraving in " Le Monde Illustre", June 5, 1886. by French School, (19th century); Private Collection; (add.info.: Fete for the wedding of Princess Marie Amelie d Orleans (1865-1951) and Duke Charles Ferdinand de Bragance (1863-1908) at the Palais Royal in Paris in 1886.
